    <dc:description>
      <dcterms:abstract xml:lang="en">Public involvement into forest management is underdeveloped in Russia due to flaws in the legislation. Challenges of Russian forest legislation and opportunities for its improvement are discussed in the article. Some regional examples are provided. Issues of FSC voluntary forest certification are discussed in the context of ensuring local communities’ interests and their involvement into the decision-making process. Recommendations to improve legislation and the draft text of the Russian forest policy document are provided.</dcterms:abstract>
    </dc:description>
